1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.366
Introducing Knox Guard domains.

2
00:00:02.366 --> 00:00:07.250
Knox Guard Domains, also known as "tenant domains", or just "domains", 

3
00:00:07.251 --> 00:00:10.633
are organizational categories designed to group customers 

4
00:00:10.634 --> 00:00:14.133
based on their specific business needs and security requirements.

5
00:00:14.333 --> 00:00:16.199
When creating a Knox Guard account, 

6
00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:19.066
users must select a domain during registration.

7
00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:22.417
This choice determines the features and capabilities available, 

8
00:00:22.417 --> 00:00:25.199
ensuring they align with the organization's goals.

9
00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:28.166
There are four primary domain types to choose from:

10
00:00:28.733 --> 00:00:33.297
The Device Financing domain is intended for businesses such as carriers or retailers

11
00:00:33.297 --> 00:00:36.129
that allow customers to pay for devices in installments,

12
00:00:36.129 --> 00:00:39.699
or carriers that want to lock in their own plans in connection with subsidies.

13
00:00:40.266 --> 00:00:44.432
This domain includes unique solutions to help reduce the risks associated with 

14
00:00:44.433 --> 00:00:48.989
installment-based and subsidized sales, such as remote device locking or

15
00:00:48.990 --> 00:00:52.099
restricting device usage to a specific carrier or SIM.

16
00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:55.380
The Device Insurance domain is designed for insurance companies

17
00:00:55.380 --> 00:00:57.578
or device protection providers 

18
00:00:57.578 --> 00:00:59.733
who want to protect customer data for lost devices,

19
00:00:59.733 --> 00:01:03.234
and reduce compensation payouts from fraudulent insurance claims.

20
00:01:03.234 --> 00:01:07.732
This domain includes features to remotely lock devices to prevent information leakage, 

21
00:01:07.733 --> 00:01:11.299
or completely wipe device information if devices can't be recovered.

22
00:01:12.033 --> 00:01:14.846
The Enterprise domain is ideal for organizations who 

23
00:01:14.847 --> 00:01:17.660
want to distribute corporate devices to their employees.

24
00:01:17.660 --> 00:01:20.404
With this domain, you can lock devices that haven’t been 

25
00:01:20.405 --> 00:01:22.633
returned after employees leave the company,

26
00:01:22.633 --> 00:01:27.069
completely wipe device information on lost devices to protect corporate data,

27
00:01:27.070 --> 00:01:30.233
or send messages to employees using notifications.

28
00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:34.773
The Other domain is designed for unique use cases that don't 

29
00:01:34.773 --> 00:01:36.965
fit any of the predefined categories. 

30
00:01:36.966 --> 00:01:39.973
Enterprises can work directly with a Samsung account rep 

31
00:01:39.974 --> 00:01:42.333
to configure features according to their needs. 

32
00:01:43.566 --> 00:01:46.966
To learn more about Knox Guard domains, see our other videos in the series,

33
00:01:46.966 --> 00:01:50.499
or check out our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com.

34
00:01:50.966 --> 00:01:52.366
Thanks for watching!

